@Node "wav.datatype()" "wav.datatype/wav.datatype"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
	wav.datatype -- data type for wave sounds.

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
	The wav data type, a sub-class of the @{"sound.datatype" Link "sound_dtc/sound.datatype()"}, is used
	to load and save wave files.

@{b}    METHODS@{ub}
	OM_NEW -- Create a new sound object from a wave file.   Creating an 
            empty object (DTST_RAM) is also supported and allows you to create
            wave files.

        DTM_WRITE -- For DTWM_RAW a wave file will be created. DTWM_IFF is 
            passed to the superclass.

@{b}    BUGS@{ub}
        Supports PCM-, (IMA/DVI) ADPCM-, MULAW- and ALAW- encoded wave files with
        either 8 or 16 bits and one or two channels. The encoder is only capable
        to save uncompressed samples (PCM). To be able to load mpeg files,
        mpega.library by Stephane Tavenard must be installed.

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"sound.datatype" Link "sound_dtc/sound.datatype()"}.

@EndNode

